# NestJS Module Patterns

## Circular Dependencies

Use `forwardRef` when two modules depend on each other:

```typescript
// In ModuleA
imports: [forwardRef(() => ModuleB)]

// In services with circular deps
constructor(
  @Inject(forwardRef(() => OtherService))
  private readonly otherService: OtherService,
) {}
```

## Optional Dependencies

Use `@Optional()` when a dependency may not be available:

```typescript
constructor(
  @Optional()
  @Inject(RedisService)
  private readonly redisService: RedisService | null,
) {}

// Always check before using
if (this.redisService) {
  await this.redisService.set(key, value);
}
```

## Module Structure

```typescript
@Module({
  imports: [
    // External modules first
    TypeOrmModule.forFeature([Entity]),
    // Then internal modules
    forwardRef(() => RelatedModule),
  ],
  controllers: [MyController],
  providers: [MyService, MyRepository],
  exports: [MyService], // Only export what other modules need
})
export class MyModule {}
```

## Global Modules

Use sparingly. Mark with `@Global()` only for truly cross-cutting concerns (Redis, Config, Metrics).
